  <div class="comment-content">

    <div class="edit-comment-hide">
      <div class="js-comment-body comment-body markdown-body markdown-format">
          <p>Looks good to me:</p>

<pre><code> To: skx/lumail &lt;lumail@noreply.github.com&gt;
 From: Raphaël Rigo&lt;notifications@github.com&gt;
 Date: Mon, 22 Jul 2013 06:14:53 -0700
 Subject: Re: [lumail] Mail subjects aren't decoded. (#66)
</code></pre>

<p>(This from the mail notification I received on your comment.)</p>

<p>I suspect here the issue is the terminal not matching ISO-8859-1 - since I don't set any character set / output encoding explicitly and all the mails I've tested are UTF-8 which matches my terminal.</p>

<p>So there's two distinct steps we should have:</p>

<ul>
<li>Decoding the header.</li>
<li>Encoding for display.</li>
</ul><p>I've only done the first.</p>
