      <div class="js-comment-body comment-body markdown-body markdown-format">
          <p>vmime is in Debian.</p>

<p>I think embedding a library is bad. Parsing is notably hard and prone to security bugs, which is problematic when libraries are embedded.</p>

<p>The problem with hacking a solution is think mail clients are among the worst pieces of software ever written ... we're likely going to encounter every possible misinterpretation from the RFCs. Reimplementing hacks to handle all those cases one more time is a waste of time... and let's not forget the risks of getting it wrong and introducing vulnerabilities.</p>
